    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"NRG1 and its receptors ErbB2 and ErbB4 are associated with cholinergic C-bouton afferents on ventral horn MNs.\"\n\nFig.4: \"Ultrastructural immunolocalization of NRG1 at C-type synapses on spinal cord MNs\"\n- \"All procedures gave the same result, showing an exquisite localization of NRG1 within the postsynaptic subsurface cistern in association with MN C termini (Fig. 4A-E). \". Experimental description: Fig.1: \" NRG1-immunopositive spots decorated the soma and proximal dendrites of large MNs at a density of 16.20 ± 2.18/100 μm of somatic perimeter (n=67 somata from P90 mice). \"\nFig.4: \"To determine the subcellular localization of NRG1 in MN central synapses, high-resolution immunoelectron microcopy was performed in samples of adult mouse spinal cord \"",
